{"cursor":"14835","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"A 'psychiatric assessment', or 'psychological screening', is a process of\ngathering information about a person within a psychiatric (or mental health)\nservice, with the purpose of making a diagnosis. The assessment is usually the\nfirst stage of a treatment process, but psychiatric assessments may also be\nused for various legal purposes. The assessment includes social and\nbiographical information, direct observations, and data from specific\npsychological tests. It is typically carried out by a psychiatrist, but it\ncould be a multi-disciplinary process involving nurses, psychologists,\noccupational therapists and social workers.\n","linknr":243,"url":"Psychiatric_assessment","recorded":1362580364,"links":12,"instances":["law","science"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Psychiatric assessment","Medical diagnosis"],"headings":["Purpose","History","Mental status examination","Physical examination","Physical investigations","Assessment tools","Multidisciplinary assessment","Other perspectives","See also","Notes","References","External links"],"image":["//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["competence","law"],["objectivity","science"]],"members":["competence","objectivity"],"related":["Psychiatric","Diagnosis","Psychiatrist","Nurse","Psychologist","Occupational_therapist","Social_worker","Therapeutic","Clinical_formulation","Forensic_psychiatry","Competence_(law)","Litigation","Damages","Child_protection","Child_abuse","Parenting","Foster_care","Psychiatric_history","Patient","Symptom","Mini-mental_state_examination","Body_mass_index","Vital_signs","Pallor","Nutritional_deficiencies","Lymphadenopathy","Abdominal_examination","Cardiovascular_system","Respiratory_examination","Neurological_examination","Thyroid-stimula